         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ For report as to the best means of obtaining a supply of these seeds....</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">83.01.25<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Thomas Wilson<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Z83/835, unit 1403, VPRS 3991/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The item is a minute on a letter from R. Murray Smith to J. Grant, 15 December 1883, enclosing a letter,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>30 November 1882,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">from<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>D. Horowitz, Forest Conservator, of West Kensington, to J. Cashel Hoey, of the Agent General's Department, London.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Horowitz had received a request from the Danish Government asking for a report on the 'feasability of rearing Eucalypts in the Danish possessions of the West Indies and which species' he would recommend, and authorising him to buy suitable seeds. He had been unable to buy seeds and so was writing to Hoey to see if he could obtain the following seeds: ½ lb of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">E. globulus</seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and ¼ each of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">E. platyphylla</seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">E. obliqua</seg>. He was still collecting information for his report but as the species named 'will grow almost anywhere' wished to at least start with them. The seeds were<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to be delivered<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the Governor of Santa Cruz, Christiansted, West Indies, at that<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>time the capital of the Danish West Indies. In 1917 Denmark sold the territory to the United States of America, and it is now known as the United States Virgin Islands.</p>
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Murray Smith had '</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">no</seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>doubt you will be happy to comply with the wishes of His Danish Majesty's Government, and I would draw to your attention that Mr Horowitz's suggestion as to forwarding it here', i.e. rather than direct to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the Danish<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>West Indies.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>For report as to the best means of obtaining a supply of these seeds.</p>
         </div>
